<br>
Magician Issues<br>
<br>
There were many vocal magicians at the forum and the big topics included Improved Invisibility, a comment Brad McQuaid made about changing Call of the Hero, and pet issues. Improved Invis wasn't given to Mages initially because they got the Monster Summoning series of spells which has only resulted in lots of people complaining about various things regarding them. He seemed put off about making new 'cool' ideas because of this but I think myself and others in attendance made it clear that many of us liked cool magical effects. Nevertheless it's possible that Magicians will be getting Improved Invis just so that they will stop talking about it. <br>
<br>
Call of the Hero has not been brought up for discussion of being nerfed at this time with the Live Team but the mages in attendance were most adamant that they wished it to retain its current properties as it was a very important 'role defining' spell for them on the high-end raids. Pet issues are in large part pathing issues and most pathing problems are fixed and he challenged players to give him an example of an Epic encounter that resulted in a pet-train. He asserted that there is no reason why mages, necros, etc. can't use pets on a major raid and that players were just paranoid about them from times past. <br>
<br>
It's 'very possible' that the Shard of the Core spell will summon a tradeable shard in the future (it is currently no-drop). <br>
<br>
The Deafening Decoy spell might be looked at 'after Luclin'.<br>
